  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IFC&apos;&apos;s involvement in this project would allow it to positively impact the market place by contributing to the development of a strong local pension system in Mexico, Chile, Colombia, Peru and Uruguay. This is of the outmost importance as pension funds plays a critical role in terms of generating long term financial resources for investments in priority sectors of the economy such as infrastructure among others. At the same time, the development of pension systems and capital markets are closely interrelated. As pension funds grow, new financial instruments are developed to meet their needs and to fill perceived gaps in the market, facilitating the growth and modernization of the local capital markets.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project is intended to strengthen Latin America&apos;&apos;s private pension fund management industry in a regionally integrated manner by supporting Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana S.A (GrupoSura) in its expansion plan.</narrative>
  </description>
